strings:
<voice_0x01000D2F><se_low>*: Well, well, if it ain't old Yangus!
Ain't seen your mush round 'ere for a while.
Got some knocked-off gear you wanna get rid of, 'ave ya?

<voice_0x01000D30><se_low>Yangus: Nah, mate! Washed me 'ands of all that.
I'm travellin' round wiv the guv'ner 'ere now.

<voice_0x01000D31><se_low>Yangus: But that's not why I'm 'ere.
That legless old runt Mitts was in 'ere before sellin' you an 'orse an' cart, weren't 'e?

<voice_0x01000D32><se_low>Yangus: It's just that we need 'em back.
They belong to the guv 'ere, see.
Mitts only went an' 'alf-inched 'em!
<voice_0x01000D33><se_low>Yangus: I gave 'im the squeeze, an' 'e said 'e sold 'em to you. That's why we're 'ere.

<voice_0x01000D34><se_low>*: You 'ad 'em pinched by Mitts!? You!?
You must be goin' soft Yangus, gettin' stitched up by someone like 'im!

<voice_0x01000D35><se_low>*: Yeah, 'e was 'ere sellin' the 'orse 'n' cart.
I gave 'im a good price for 'em.

<voice_0x01000D36><se_low>*: So I did have 'em, but...
I dunno 'ow to tell ya this...
I sold 'em already.

<voice_0x01000D37><se_low>Yangus: You wot!? Who to?
We need 'em back, desperate like!

<voice_0x01000D38><se_low>*: Well...
I dunno 'ow to tell ya this either...
I sold 'em to Red.
<voice_0x01000D39><se_low>Yangus: YOU WOT!?

<voice_0x01000D3A><se_low>Yangus: Red!?
The old artful dodger 'erself!?
Yer 'avin' a giraffe, intcha?

<voice_0x01000D3B><se_low>*: Sorry Yangus, straight up.
Look, it's out o' my 'ands now.
You'll 'ave to sort it out yerself.

<voice_0x01000D3C><se_low>Yangus: I don't believe it!
Now Red's mixed up in all this...

<voice_0x01000D3D><se_low>Yangus: It's the last thing I wanna do right now,
but we're gonna 'ave to pay 'er a visit.

<voice_0x01000D3E><se_low>Yangus: She lives in a gaff south-west o' town.
Nice little pad, it is.
Slap bang wallop in the middle of a lake.

<voice_0x01000D3F><se_low>Yangus: Come on, guv! If we wanna 'elp the 'orse-princess, that's where we gotta 'ead.
To the south-west!

<se_low>*: Well there's a turn-up for the books.
The lone wolf decides she's gonna join a pack, eh? I've seen it all now!

<se_low>*: Blow me down, ya managed to get ol' Red
to give ya yer 'orse back! Yer persistent blokes,
I'll give ya that much.
<se_low>*: I knew it! T'be honest, this is the first time I've ever laid eyes on one.

<se_low>*: Ya can't fool me.
I know an alchemy pot when I see one.
<se_low>*: What's this, you've already got yerself <INDEF_ART_SGL_I_NAME_2>?
<se_low>*: It's a deal, then!
<Cap><leader> trades <DEF_ART_SGL_I_NAME_2> for Dodgy Dave's <SGL_I_NAME_1>!

<se_low>*: No go, eh? Ah well, too bad.
I ain't gonna try an' twist yer arm.
<se_low>*: I knew it! T'be honest, this is the first time I've ever laid eyes on one.

<se_low>*: Ya can't fool me.
I know an alchemy pot when I see one.

<se_low>*: Right then, I've got a new order for ya.
How about you cook me up <INDEF_ART_SGL_I_NAME_2>?
<se_low>*: Eh!? You've already got yerself <INDEF_ART_SGL_I_NAME_2>? Cor, you're a fast one!
<se_low>*: Eh? You still ain't managed to cook me up <INDEF_ART_SGL_I_NAME_2>?
<se_low>*: I can't give ya a new order until you've done that. And it goes wivout sayin' that I can't give ya my <SGL_I_NAME_1> unless you wanna make a trade.
<se_low>*: Ah, so you've brought me <INDEF_ART_SGL_I_NAME_2>, eh?

<se_low>*: Sorry for sellin' off yer 'orse like that.
Lemme make it up to ya.
How'd ya like to make a little dough, eh?

<se_low>*: Ev'ry now an' then, I got me mitts on
some rare stuff, and before I knew it I 'ad
a reputation to uphold.
<se_low>*: Here's what I'm proposin'. When I 'ear about somefin' a customer wants, I'll give you an order an' you cook it up for me in yer pot.

<se_low>*: So? Pretty juicy, eh?
I mean, 'ow can ya say no to that, eh?
<se_low>*: Oh, an' before I forget. Even if ya don't wanna sell, bring the stuff ya make over 'ere anyhow so I can take a look. I'll make it worth your while.

o' yours comes into the picture.
